The paper deals with quantization of frame coefficients, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of sub-Gaussian random variables is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.MM). The application of the results to compressed sensing also suggests the possibility of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
